description: This issue introduces Itoko no ie de or 従姉妹の家で meaning "In Cousin's House", commonly called "At My Cousin's House" in the West. The story stars Hiroto, who goes to visit his aunt, and her daughters Akemi and Mari. This was later included as chapter 3 of Doutei Senka or 童貞専科 meaning "Virgin Special Course" released the same year.

In the year 2047, Suske tries to deal with the apparant death of Wiske. In 2017, Lambik and Jerom try to find Barabas who is kidnapped by Krimson. Krimson has forced Barabas to transport him to the year 2047 where Krimson tries to put an end to Suske and Wiske.
name: Jérusalum

description: When the caped heroes of the world's safest city inexplicably all turn into homicidal lunatics, no one is safe.
The Tower is under siege--by a foe determined to take down the team, and anyone else foolish enough to believe training a new generation of heroes was a good idea!
name: Titans, Part 3 of 4

description: It's Josie & The Pussycats like you've never seen them before -- manga style! Join Josie, Valerie and Melody in this retelling of how they became one of the biggest bands in America. Starting off as everyday high school students, these three girls are ready to take on the world with the power of rock! Enjoy over 70 pages of laughs as these Pussycats claw their way to the big time!
name: TPB

volume.name: Josie & The Pussycats: The Complete Manga!

description:
Richard can’t stop thinking about the clock. He lies in bed each night listening to its tick-tocking, to the pendulum’s heavy swing. Why does his grand-dad open its old doors in secret and walk into the darkness beyond?

One night, too inquisitive to sleep, Richard tiptoes from his bed, opens the cherry wood door of the grandfather clock, and steps inside. There, in a strange, nebulous twilight, he sees the face of the Earth, locked forever in a simulated world, where green things seem to grow in the semblance of trees and plants, from unreal soil.

In this quasi-world they sit together for many nights, the face and the boy, talking quietly of creation and the beginning of all things. Moved by the face’s ancient tale of mysterious, magnetic love, Richard longs to release him. So one night he secretly winds back the hands of the grandfather clock, and changes time forever…
name: HC
The Island of the Laughing Waters

description:
Forget J. K. Rowling. Forget Lemony Snicket. Forget Phillip Pullman. Christopher Grahame is the premier children's author of the twenty-first century.

From a handful of homespun tales told to his own children at bedtime, Chris Grahame is now a publishing phenomenon. With his work translated into everything from Aborigine to Zulu, he is the cornerstone of a multi-million dollar, franchise-spewing empire. Is it any surprise then that under all this pressure something has to give? Unfortunately, it's Chris's mind.

Stricken by mysterious headaches and blackouts that plagued his childhood, Chris once again finds himself walking the avenues and boulevards of Castrovalva-the fantasy realm he dreamt up as a boy, to while away his recuperation. But like Chris, Castrovalva has also changed. Deluged in mud, blood, and barbed wire, war has come to wonderland. Chris tries to tell himself it's all a bad dream ... so why can't he wake up?

Ian Edginton and D'Israeli also collaborated on Scarlet Traces, which Entertainment Weekly gave an "A" grade, calling it "bold and shattering."
name: HC

volume.name: Fist of the North Star Part Two
